panels.description:
[🧐High-cardinality data]
Identify 25 longest running API Gateway requests in your API Gateway access log group.

targets.expression:
filter ispresent(responseLatency)
| fields @timestamp, @message, @xrayTraceId, requestId, ip, apiKey, requestTime, httpMethod, routeKey, path, status, protocol, integrationStatus, integrationLatency, responseLatency, responseLength
| parse @message "(*) *" as @requestId, restOfMessage
| parse restOfMessage "Method completed with status: *" as @status
| parse restOfMessage "Received response. Status: *, Integration latency: * ms" as responseStatus, jsonIntegrationLatency
| sort responseLatency desc
| display path, responseLatency, httpMethod, requestId, @timestamp
| limit 25

panels.title: 🔴API-Gateway🏰: Longest Running Requests (Top 25)

targets.expression:
filter ispresent(status)
| filter status >= 400 and status <= 599
| stats count() as errorCount by path, status, httpMethod, ip
| sort errorCount desc
| limit 25

panels.description:
[🧐High-cardinality data]
Get list of most popular API paths in your API Gateway access log group

targets.expression:
filter ispresent(path)
| stats count(*) as requestCount by path
| sort requestCount desc
| limit 25

panels.title: 🔴API-Gateway🎭: Most popular API paths (Top 25)

panels.description:
[🧐RED - Duration]
Duration (Percentiles p99, p95, p90, p75) - [Filtered by ${lambda_log_group}]

links.title: This is dummy link to avoid mistaken click

targets.expression:
filter @type = "REPORT"
| stats
  avg(@billedDuration) as Average,
  percentile(@billedDuration, 99) as NinetyNinth,
  percentile(@billedDuration, 95) as NinetyFifth,
  percentile(@billedDuration, 90) as Ninetieth,
  percentile(@billedDuration, 75) as SeventyFifth
by bin(5m)
targets.label: ${PROP('Dim.FunctionName')}

targets.expression:
filter eventSource like /cognito-idp.amazonaws.com/
| filter eventName like	/InitiateAuth|RespondToAuthChallenge/
| filter recipientAccountId in ["${account_ids}"]
| fields @timestamp, @logStream, @message, eventVersion, userIdentity.type, coalesce(userIdentity.invokedBy, userIdentity.principalId, userIdentity.accountId) as InvokedBy, eventTime, eventSource, eventName, eventType, awsRegion, sourceIPAddress, userAgent, errorCode, errorMessage, eventID, @requestParameters, additionalEventData, requestID, readOnly, eventType, apiVersion, managementEvent, recipientAccountId, recipientAccountId.serviceEventDetails.serviceAccountId, eventCategory, tlsDetails.tlsVersion, tlsDetails.cipherSuite, tlsDetails.clientProvidedHostHeader
| stats count(*) as totalAttempts
| sort @timestamp desc
#| limit ${limit}
